  <front>
   <head>SCOTCH BALLAD.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, , by thy winding stream</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">How once I lov'd to stray,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And view the morning's redd'ning beam,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Or charm of closing day!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To yon dear grot by  side,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">How oft my steps were led;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where far beneath the waters glide,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And thick the woods are spread!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But I no more a charm can see</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">In  lovely glades;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And drear and desolate to me</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Are those enchanting shades.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">While far â€” how far from  bowers,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">My wand'ring lover flies;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where dark the angry tempest lowers,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And high the billows rise!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And O, where'er the wand'rer goes,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Is that poor mourner dear,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who gives, while soft the  flows,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Each passing wave a tear?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And does he now that grotto view?</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">On those steep banks still gaze?</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In fancy does he still pursue</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The  lovely maze?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O come! repass the stormy wave,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">O toil for gold no more!</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Our love a dearer pleasure gave</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">On  peaceful shore.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Leave not my breaking heart to mourn</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The joys so long denied;</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ah, soon to those green banks return,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Where  meets the .</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
